title.narrative: C1: At least 300 stakeholders trained in biosafety and IPR by the end of the project

comment.narrative: Five regional training modules have already been organized with more than 250 participants, including national trainers(train-the-trainers). The replication of the regional trainings at the national level planned before the end of the year.

title.narrative: A1: At least 50 researchers trained in scientific methodologies on risk assessment and management

comment.narrative: No new training session organized since for. End target already completed.

title.narrative: At least 25% of trained researchers and other stakeholders apply the knowledge they have acquired in their activities related to biosafety by the end of the project

comment.narrative: Since 2012 the capacity building action plan has been completed, and more than 250 researchers and stakeholders have been trainedin various aspects related to biosafety (detection, inspection and control, risk assessment, communication on risk and awarenessraising, IPR..) and it is expected that 25 % of the participants apply the knowledge that they have acquired; a survey will beconducted before May 2014 to determine the percentage of people applying knowledge .

title.narrative: A1: At least 5 national laboratories fully equipped at the end of the project

comment.narrative: UEMOA has delivered all the laboratory equipment planed to be delivered before June 2013. 100% as completion rate for thenational laboratories. A contract is signed on April 2013 to deliver the equipment for the regional laboratory based in Ouagadougou; at date the construction completed and equipment is ongoing.
